The paper proposes a modified co-training method using deep neural networks for hyperspectral image classification. This involves feature extraction using a recurrent neural network (RNN) and a convolutional neural network (CNN), which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of k-means clustering, which is a common unsupervised learning technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper involves the use of semi-supervised learning, which is a topic in both neural networks (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
